cs.IT, cs.SP, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal denoising, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of the Stein's unbiased risk estimate (SURE) and the optimization of the denoiser within a parametric class suggest a machine learning (cs.LG) perspective. The linear parameterization of the denoiser and the use of different kernel families suggest a numerical analysis (cs.NA) approach. Finally, the mention of the Bayesian optimal performance and the use of MMSE estimators suggest a statistics (cs.MM) perspective.
